# Test DSL — assertion words (a4 layer)
#
# Built on the existing Any vocabulary (`assert`, `assert-eq`, `<=`, `>=`)
# and the test-primitive word `capture-data`. These compose to cover the
# Phase 2 assertion set from the test-DSL plan.

# assert-max  ( Int Int -- Int )
# Ensure the value under TOS is <= the bound at TOS. Leaves the value.
# Usage:  result 5 assert-max   # expects result <= 5, leaves result.
: assert-max Int Int -> Int ;
    2dup <= assert
    drop
.

# assert-min  ( Int Int -- Int )
# Ensure the value under TOS is >= the bound at TOS. Leaves the value.
# Usage:  result 0 assert-min   # expects result >= 0, leaves result.
: assert-min Int Int -> Int ;
    2dup >= assert
    drop
.
